extendedInfo.description: Do you love Primo?  Do you want to play games with him as the star?  Well now you can!  With this great app you will be able to play Primomemory, jigsaw puzzles, and Tetris.  You will love spending some free time with Primo.Edwin "Eddie" Carlos ColÃ³n (born December 21, 1982) is a Puerto Rican professional wrestler. He is currently signed by WWE wrestling as Primo. Other members of ColÃ³n's family have also been involved in the World Wrestling Council, including his uncle JosÃ© ColÃ³n and cousin Orlando ColÃ³n who have been involved in several angles within the company.ColÃ³n debuted on 1999, wrestling in the Cruiserweight division. His feud with Steele continued for a month, during which he dropped and recovered the title on March 10, 2001. He feuded over the title for six months, losing and winning it once. By autumn, ColÃ³n was involved in a storyline involving Justin Sane, continuing a similar pattern. In early 2002, ColÃ³n was involved in a storyline with Rey Mysterio, Jr., who defeated ColÃ³n for the title on January 6, 2002. Mysterio held the title for two months before dropping it back on April 6, 2002, which marked ColÃ³n's final Junior Championship reign. One week later on November 6, 2004, ColÃ³n defeated El Bronco and won the Universal Heavyweight Championship for the first time in his career. He then entered a feud with El Diamante, eventually dropping the title to him. In late 2006, ColÃ³n signed a developmental contract with WWE. The team was victorious, winning the promotion's Television Tag Team Championship. On March 5, 2006 he participated in WCW Saturday Night tribute show World Wrestling Legends: 6:05 The Reunion when he face Vampiro.
